Biography
 Kravis received his Bachelor's degree in Economics from Claremont McKenna College in 1967 and interned with money management firm, Madison Fund. He went on to obtain his MBA from Columbia University in 1969. Served as Vice President of Katy Industries, a New York-based stock exchange company, and was responsible for designing and implementing acquisition programs. Kravis then joined Bear Stearns where his cousin, George Roberts, and Jerome Kohlberg were working, and served as a Partner until 1976. In 1976, Kravis co-founded KKR & Co. (...
