Interests, Passion, Hobbies

Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Health and Wellness
Description: Kravis and his wife Marie-Josee, reportedly donated $100 million to New York-based cancer treatment and research institute Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Stage and Theater - Performing Arts
Description: Trustee of New York City Ballet (NYCB) and Metropolitan Ballet.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Politics
Description: Generous political donor has given more than $1.2 million to Republican candidates and causes. Kravis was a major contributor during the re-election campaign of President George H. W. Bush, and was Co-Founder of the Republican Leadership Council.

Contact us to see more Interests, Passion, Hobbies
Philanthropy

Giving Profile: Kravis gives primarily to education, arts and healthcare causes. Lifetime giving exceeds $200 million. Notable gifts include $100 million to the Columbia Business School in 2010; $100 million to Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center in May 2014; and $15 million to establish the Center for Cardiovascular Health. Chairman of The Marie-Josee and Henry R. Kravis Foundation; in 2012, the foundation had $1 million in assets and $300,000 in income. Giving exceeds $21 million. Donates primarily to education, health, arts, culture and community development causes. Recipients include Claremont McKenna College, Mount Sinai Hospital, Columbia University, Rockefeller University, New York Philharmonic, Robin Hood Foundation, Eaglebrook School and Museum of Modern Art. Trustee of The Raymond & Bessie Kravis Foundation; in 2012,the foundation had $28 million in assets and $800,000 in income. Giving exceeds $800,000. Donates primarily to arts and culture, health and educational causes. Recipients include Philbrook Museum of Art, Arts and Humanities Council, University of Tulsa and St. Johns Medical Center. 

